name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
February 4, Jiangxi. A blogger found a man born in 2002 standing in front of a self-service ticket machine for 10 minutes at a train station because he couldn't afford a 26-yuan train ticket. The kind blogger bought a train ticket for him. When asked why he had no money to buy a ticket, the man said that the electronics factory had not paid his salary yet.
Later, the blogger helped an older woman buy a transfer train ticket at the train station.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content: On the evening of February 4, Xue Peng, a professor and doctoral supervisor at the Beijing Computational Science Research Center, posted a video under her real name, saying that she was deprived of her postgraduate enrollment qualifications without knowing it, and her name was no longer on the postgraduate directory starting February 1. She felt that she might have been suppressed and hoped to have a normal channel to communicate and resolve this matter.

name: 李老师不是你老师
content:
On February 5, the Beijing Computational Science Research Center issued a solemn statement in response.
The response stated that the center reserves the right to pursue legal responsibility for Professor Xue Peng and other people and media who spread rumors and misled the public.
